Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows an uneven surface slightly convex, like from a leather bag. In the break several string impressions. The side shows several finger impressions. The top bears a seal-impression with a circumferential line. Inside the top of maybe a j-reed (M17), right of it a nfr-sign, further right a mn-sign, underneath it an n and a further horizontal sign. The rest is broken off.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
